        "text": "5. An anonymous reviewer pointed out the U.S.N.O. also reports moon rise and setting times within archival data. It was noted using a sliding window of analysis based on whether the moon was above the horizon might have been an alternative approach within the analysis. Additional analyses not reported here, but available from the lead author upon request, suggest the results were not substantively different with the use of such a variable window of analysis. The original models (fixed 8:00 pm 3:00 am window of analysis) were retained for the analysis reported in this article, though the alternative scheme was included in later portions of the discussion.",
